## Acceptance Criteria

### WebSocket Backpressure
- [ ] Queue size monitored and capped at maxQueueSize
- [ ] Oldest messages dropped when queue overflows (preserves recent data)
- [ ] Backpressure signal sent to server when highWaterMark reached
- [ ] Normal flow resumes at lowWaterMark
- [ ] No memory leaks under sustained high load

### Virtualization
- [ ] Smoothly renders 100,000+ log lines
- [ ] Variable height rows supported (wrapped text)
- [ ] Scroll position maintained on data updates
- [ ] Auto-scroll to bottom when following output
- [ ] Keyboard navigation works in virtualized lists

### Bundle Size
- [ ] Initial bundle under 200KB gzipped
- [ ] Total JS under 500KB gzipped
- [ ] Vendor chunks properly split
- [ ] No duplicate dependencies in chunks
- [ ] Source maps generated but not shipped

### Lazy Loading
- [ ] All routes lazy loaded except shell
- [ ] Loading skeleton shown during chunk load
- [ ] Prefetch hints for likely navigation
- [ ] Error boundary for failed chunk loads
- [ ] Retry mechanism for network failures

### Web Workers
- [ ] Log parsing offloaded to worker
- [ ] Search indexing in worker
- [ ] Graceful fallback if workers unavailable
- [ ] Workers terminated on component unmount
- [ ] No main thread blocking for >50ms

### CI Budgets
- [ ] Bundle size check fails build if exceeded
- [ ] Lighthouse scores checked on every PR
- [ ] Performance regression alerts
- [ ] Historical performance tracking
- [ ] Budget configuration in repo

### Runtime Performance
- [ ] 60fps during normal operation
- [ ] Input latency under 100ms
- [ ] Time to Interactive under 3 seconds
- [ ] First Contentful Paint under 1.5 seconds
- [ ] Core Web Vitals pass thresholds

